HEADWORD: Laciniated
<hw>La*cin"i*a"ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Lacinia</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Fringed; having a fringed border.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Cut into deep, narrow,
irregular lobes; slashed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laciniolate</ent>⟦br⟧
